The mapred-site.xml used by bento-cluster. You can edit this file to configure
the behavior of your MapReduce cluster, jobs, etc. Outright removing one of
the variables defined here may cause errors in the clusters started by
bento-cluster.

Note that bento-cluster forces the values of certain configuration variables.
Namely, hadoop.log.dir, hadoop.working.dir, mapred.output.dir, and
hadoop.tmp.dir are controlled by bento-cluster and any values specified here
will be ignored.

